stylometry: The variables that you need to consider when determining the level of saftey stock are ROP and EDDLT. You must subtract EDDLT from the ROP in order to find saftey stock. ROP is the re-order point which tells you when you need to order more product so that you don't run out and EDDLT is the estimated demand during lead time which tells you how much the demand will be while you are processing orders for other customers. Some other variables you will need to know in order to find out these numbers are: acceptable level of stock out, average lead time, average carrying costs, and average ordering costs.
